reference: A jacket and full skirt ensemble worn in several key scenes in the 1939 movie has fetched $137,000 at auction. The has faded over time from its original slate blue-gray color to become light gray. Private collection James Tumblin learned that the dress was about to be thrown out in the 1960s and negotiated a deal to buy it for $20. Other top selling items from the auction were a straw hat worn by Leigh that sold for $52,500.

Rebbie said that he purchased the camera specifically to watch the 15-year-old girl but captured other victims on film, too. Rebbie's  is being held on a $500,000 bail and will appear in court on May 1.

reference: Boeing 747 can normally hold up to 600 people but this model was customised for a single ultra-wealthy tycoon. Digital images show how the interior is as luxurious as an expensive hotel room despite space constraints.
